<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA6FFC434FCF858F6E94FEC" bold="true" box="[136,251,1935,1957]" pageId="4" pageNumber="197">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA6FFC4348AF847F4A64FEF" authority="Chun &amp; F. Chun. A. Habit" authorityName="Chun &amp; F. Chun. A. Habit" authorityYear="1939" box="[254,692,1936,1958]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="4" pageNumber="197" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA6FFC4348AF847F7D74FEC" box="[254,453,1936,1957]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="197">Begonia hainanensis</emphasis>
Chun &amp; F.Chun.A. Habit
</taxonomicName>
and habitat; B. Habit; C. Branch, showing staminate and pistillate inflorescences; D. Stem, showing stipules and bracts; E. Staminate inflorescence; F. Pistillate inflorescences; G. Staminate flowers; H. Pistillate flowers. All photos from 
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA6FFC43553F80FF7894FA4" box="[295,411,2008,2029]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="197">Peng 19543</emphasis>
by C.-I Peng
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="41FD84BAFFA7FFC534C9FD99F41E4AB0" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0958D731FFA7FFC534C9FD99F41E4AB0" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1336]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC534C9FD99F7E14A21" bold="true" box="[189,499,590,616]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Distribution and ecology:</emphasis>
—The new species is currently known from Cý Króa Commune, M’Ðrắk District, 
<collectingRegion id="CB2319D3FFA7FFC534FCFDA5F7454AC5" box="[136,343,626,652]" country="Vietnam" name="Dak Lak" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Dak Lak Province</collectingRegion>
, Central Highlands 
<collectingCountry id="71F097A1FFA7FFC53642FDA5F4874AC5" box="[566,661,626,652]" name="Vietnam" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
and probably also occurs in adjacent areas. The new species grows on humid, moist, or rocky areas in broad-leaved evergreen forests, at elevations of 
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC5306CFD40F22B4AF9" box="[1048,1081,663,688]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">ca.</emphasis>
<quantity id="CE1F7AD4FFA7FFC53036FD41F29E4AF8" box="[1090,1164,662,689]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" unit="m" value="480.0">480 m</quantity>
, associated with 
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC53124FD40F3BE4AF8" authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[1360,1452,663,689]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC534E5FD6DF7544A9C" box="[145,326,698,725]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Arundinaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC534E5FD6DF7094A9D" box="[145,283,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Arundinaria</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC53528FD6DF7E34A9D" box="[348,497,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Gesneriaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC53677FD6DF45E4A9D" box="[515,588,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Chrita</emphasis>
sp.), 
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC536F9FD6DF5174A9D" box="[653,773,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Urticaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC53762FD6DF5AC4A9C" box="[790,958,698,725]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Elatostema" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC53762FD6DF5864A9D" box="[790,916,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Elatostema</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC537A1FD6DF2A94A9D" box="[981,1211,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Pentaphragmataceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Pentaphragmataceae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC530B8FD6DF38F4A9C" box="[1228,1437,698,725]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Pentaphragmataceae" genus="Pentaphragma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC530B8FD6DF3604A9D" box="[1228,1394,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Pentaphragma</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC534C3FD09F7774AB1" authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[183,357,734,760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Melastomaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC53502FD09F7EC4AB0" box="[374,510,734,761]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Sonerila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC53502FD09F7C74AB1" box="[374,469,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Sonerila</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="41FD84BAFFA7FFC534C9FCD5F6F34B09" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="0958D731FFA7FFC534C9FCD5F6F34B09" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1336]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC534C9FCD5F75A4B55" bold="true" box="[189,328,770,796]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet is named in honor of Mr. Nguyen Kim Long, who first discovered this new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="41FD84BAFFA7FFC534C9FC9DF6C84BBD" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="0958D731FFA7FFC534C9FC9DF6C84BBD" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1336]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC534C9FC9DF7A54B2D" bold="true" box="[189,439,842,868]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Conservation status:</emphasis>
—A small population of the new species is distributed in an area of about 
<quantity id="CE1F7AD4FFA7FFC5316FFC9DF3454B2D" box="[1307,1367,842,868]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" unit="km" value="1.0">1 km</quantity>
<superScript id="FE927A79FFA7FFC53123FC9DF34D4B11" attach="left" box="[1367,1375,842,856]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">2</superScript>
that is not included in any protected forest, therefore its survival is potentially threatened by 
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC53021FCB8F2A04BC1" box="[1109,1202,879,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC53021FCB8F2A04BC1" box="[1109,1202,879,904]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Begonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collectors and habitat degradation. However further botanical surveys are needed in this realtively unexplored area for a complete conservation assessment of this species, until then we assess 
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC536C3FC60F59A4B99" box="[695,904,950,976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kimlongii">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC536C3FC60F59A4B99" box="[695,904,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Begonia kimlongii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be Data Deficient (DD) according to 
<bibRefCitation id="6D76AAC0FFA7FFC53113FC61F6C44BBD" author="IUCN Standards" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" refId="ref2700" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2019) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. Available from: https: // www. iucnredlist. org / resources / redlistguidelines (accessed 22 March 2022)" type="url" year="2019">IUCN (2019)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="41FD84BAFFA7FFC534C9FC29F7984D71" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0958D731FFA7FFC534C9FC29F7984D71" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,1336]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC534C9FC29F71B4C51" bold="true" box="[189,265,1022,1048]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC53552FC28F7E34C51" box="[294,497,1022,1048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kimlongii">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC53552FC28F7E34C51" box="[294,497,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Begonia kimlongii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinctive for its dimorphic bracts that are relatively unusual in 
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC530B4FC28F2CB4C51" box="[1216,1241,1023,1048]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">B.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC53160FC28F3B74C51" box="[1300,1445,1023,1048]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Petermannia</emphasis>
. However, it is a typical member of the section in having a cane-like habit, 3-locular ovary with bifid placentae, and protogynous inflorescences. This new species is related to 
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC5375EFB90F3B94C29" authority="Nguyen &amp; Tebbitt (2005: 248)" authorityName="H. Q. Nguyen &amp; Tebbitt. A, B. Habits" authorityPageNumber="248" authorityYear="2005" box="[810,1451,1094,1121]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cucphuongensis">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC5375EFB90F2564C29" box="[810,1092,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">Begonia cucphuongensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6D76AAC0FFA7FFC53039FB90F3B94C29" author="Nguyen, H. Q. &amp; Tebbitt, M. C." box="[1101,1451,1094,1121]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" pagination="247 - 251" refId="ref3183" refString="Nguyen, H. Q. &amp; Tebbitt, M. C. (2005) An unusual new species of Begonia (Begoniaceae) from Vietnam. Gardens' Bulletin Singapore 57: 247 - 251." type="journal article" year="2005">Nguyen &amp; Tebbitt (2005: 248)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in its cane-like habit, sparsely hairy stem, adaxially glabrous leaves and the number of staminate tepals. It is readily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC5352BFB58F4224CE1" authorityName="H. Q. Nguyen &amp; Tebbitt. A, B. Habits" authorityYear="2005" box="[351,560,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cucphuongensis">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC5352BFB58F4224CE1" box="[351,560,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">B. cucphuongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its oblanceolate to obovate (vs. lanceolate to narrowly ovate) leaves, terminal inflorescences (vs. axillary, rarely terminal) and pistillate flowers with 5 tepals (vs. 3). Moreover, it resembles 
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC531E7FB64F4DB4CB9" authority="Souvannakhoummane et al. (2016: 2)" authorityName="Souvannakhoummane" authorityPageNumber="2" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lamxayiana">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC531E7FB64F7194CB9" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">B. lamxayiana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6D76AAC0FFA7FFC53561FB01F4DB4CB9" author="Souvannakhoummane, K. &amp; Hughes, M. &amp; Lanorsavanh, S." box="[277,713,1238,1264]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref3511" refString="Souvannakhoummane, K., Hughes, M. &amp; Lanorsavanh, S. (2016) Begonia lamxayiana Souvann. (Begoniaceae): a new species from Laos. Thai Journal of Botany 8 (1): 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="2016">
Souvannakhoummane 
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC5366CFB00F4464CB9" box="[536,596,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">et al.</emphasis>
(2016: 2)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CEE7ACB2FFA7FFC53772FB00F2F24CB9" authority="Chun &amp; Chun (1939: 20)" authorityName="Chun &amp; F. Chun. A. Habit" authorityPageNumber="20" authorityYear="1939" box="[774,1248,1238,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis id="3B930B23FFA7FFC53772FB00F5BC4CB9" box="[774,942,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="198">B. hainanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6D76AAC0FFA7FFC537CDFB01F2F24CB9" author="Chun, W. Y. &amp; Chun, F." box="[953,1248,1238,1264]" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" pagination="20 - 28" refId="ref2546" refString="Chun, W. Y. &amp; Chun, F. (1939) Notes on Begonia. Sunyatsenia 4 (1 - 2): 20 - 28." type="journal article" year="1939">Chun &amp; Chun (1939: 20)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
which also share oblanceolate leaves, lax inflorescences and 3-locular ovaries. A comparison of the salient characters of the four species is presented in 
<tableCitation id="4465E28AFFA7FFC53544FAC9F7964D71" box="[304,388,1310,1336]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="5.[136,224,1384,1408]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of Begonia kimlongii T.S.Hoang, V.C.Nguyen &amp; C.W.Lin, B. cucphuongensis H.Q.Nguyen &amp; Tebbitt, B. hainanensis Chun &amp; F.Chun and B. lamxayiana Souvann." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/5D9887B9FFA7FFC534FCFABFF5754DED" pageId="5" pageNumber="198" tableUuid="5D9887B9FFA7FFC534FCFABFF5754DED">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
